- Used TPromise<any> to allow any pick object return type, okay?

Summary:
Uses extended quickOpenWidget.show() instead of .pick()
- Generalized changes to support other clients with new IShowOptions
- Maintain current operation for existing clients
- Added options for IShowOptions
- openOnSelection : returns pick, skips open if false (normal default is true, opens pick)
- historyFilter : provide scheme filter (file, untitled) and resource name excludes
- inputPlaceHolder : input box inputPlaceHolder

export interface IShowOptions {
	quickNavigateConfiguration?: IQuickNavigateConfiguration;
	inputSelection?: { start: number; end: number; };
	openOnSelection?: boolean;
	historyFilter?: { resourceType: string[], exclude: string[] };
	inputPlaceHolder?: string;
}
 
- Added PICK mode , does not open selected, returns pick object

export enum Mode {
	PREVIEW,
	OPEN,
	OPEN_IN_BACKGROUND,
	PICK
}

- If in pick mode, return entire pick object in promise
